@page "/security"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Security - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">Legal</span>
        <h1>Security</h1>
        <p>Security is built into grow.IT through authenticated access controls, tenant-aware data boundaries, and auditable operational workflows.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-grid-section">
        <div class="contact-grid">
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Access Controls</h2>
                <p>Role-based authorization and session controls restrict access to the minimum permissions required for each user role.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Data Protection</h2>
                <p>Security headers, controlled API access, and backend validation help protect data in transit and reduce exposure risk.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Auditability</h2>
                <p>Administrative actions and unauthorized access attempts are logged to support incident review and governance workflows.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>Responsible Disclosure</h2>
            <p>If you identify a potential vulnerability, contact us immediately with reproduction details so we can triage and remediate quickly.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>Need security or compliance details?</h2>
            <p>We can share additional implementation and control context for review workflows.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?subject=Security%20Question" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Security Team</a>
                <a href="/privacy" class="btn btn-outline">Read Privacy Policy</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
